<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="75.[781,1374,1278,1706]" pageId="75" pageNumber="470">
Based on morphology, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1907" box="[1118,1231,1396,1429]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sylvisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="75" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="granti">S. granti</taxonomicName>
is considered the most primitive species of 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sylvisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="75" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sylvisorex</taxonomicName>
, but genetic data placed it close to S. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sylvisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="75" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lunaris">lunaris</taxonomicName>
. Subspecies might be distinct species. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
